//
// test/Lower/m3_corpus/s09/pass.test — M5 T106 / FR-030 / SC-003.
// Auto-generated golden-diff harness paired with pass.expected.mlir.
// Asserts `nslc -emit=mlir` on the M3 Sema pass-case fixture for
// constraint S09 (`for` loop variable must be a reg) produces byte-
// identical output to the captured golden.
//
// Originally XFAIL'd because the visitor's `lowerExpr(LiteralExpr)`
// defaulted unsized literals to `!nsl.bits<1>`, producing a verifier
// error on `for (i := 0; i < 8; i++)` (`nsl.constant 8` doesn't fit
// in `!nsl.bits<1>`). The lowerExpr `typeHint` plumbing introduced
// in this fix-bug pass propagates the loop-var's type through the
// comparison's RHS, so the literal `8` widens to `!nsl.bits<8>`.
// Test re-enabled.
//
// RUN: %nslc -emit=mlir %S/../../../sema/s09/pass.nsl > %t.actual.mlir
// RUN: diff %t.actual.mlir %S/pass.expected.mlir
